<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910326-0146</DOCNO><DOCID>910326-0146.</DOCID><HL>   Calton Reaches Pact With Banks</HL><DATE>03/26/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   CN</CO><IN>HOME CONSTRUCTION (HOM)</IN><LP>   FREEHOLD, N.J. -- Housing developer Calton Inc. said itreached a pact for bank lenders to refrain from taking anyaction against the company until June 30 for defaulting onloan payments.   In November, Calton defaulted on $10 million of principalpayments due under secured credit agreement with the banks,and has been prevented by the banks from making interest andprincipal payments to bondholders totaling $9.8 million.</LP><TEXT>   Under the latest agreement, Calton said its allowablemonthly borrowings will be tied to land and housing sales, ata slightly higher interest rate. Also, the company said it isprohibited from paying dividends, incurring additional debt,and, except for certain circumstances, acquiring land withoutthe consent of the lenders.</TEXT></DOC>